// After creating this, in VS Code click the environment name in the bottom-right status bar 
// (or Ctrl+Shift+P → "Rest Client: Switch Environment") and pick dev — that's what makes {{baseUrl}} etc. resolve.
// baseurl or usertoken , admin token , categoryid , productid , ticketid , addressid in .vscode/settings.json

### Create Category (admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "Electronics",
  "description": "Electronic gadgets and devices"
}

### Get All Categories (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/categories

### Get Single Category (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/categories/{{categoryId}}

### Update Category (admin only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/categories/{{categoryId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "description": "Updated description"
}

### Delete Category (admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/categories/{{categoryId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}